p: In Greece, a much higher rate of SFSV-NT-Ab was observed (71.9%) compared with 4.4% and 2.6% for TOSV and ARBV, respectively ( Table 1 and Fig 1). Similar results were observed in Cyprus where SFSV-NT-Ab was present in 60.2% of the dog sera, whereas 16.3%, 8.4% and 5.4% of sera were positive for ADAV, TOSV and ARBV, respectively ( Table 2 and Fig 2).
